text.section:
The owner of a vehicle, or a lessee of the vehicle under a lease not intended as security, or a director, officer, employee, or partner of a business entity that owns the vehicle considered eligible by the Administration may apply to the Administration for the assignment of a commemorative registration plate under this section if the vehicle is included in one of the following classes:
A Class A (passenger) vehicle;
A Class E (truck) vehicle with a manufacturer's rated capacity of one ton or less;
A Class G (trailer) vehicle; or
A Class M (multipurpose) vehicle.
